law.text:
As used in KRS 150.725 to 150.735:
"Permit" means a permit to hold captive cervids;
"Applicant" means a person or entity who has applied to the department for a permit to hold captive cervids;
"Application" means an application to obtain a permit to hold captive cervids;
"Hold" means to confine to a facility regulated under KRS 150.725 to 150.735;
"Import" means to knowingly bring a captive cervid into the state for the purpose of that captive cervid remaining in the state or being slaughtered in the state. "Import" shall not include transporting a captive cervid into the state for the purpose of transporting that captive cervid through the state to a location out of the state. A captive cervid specified in this subsection shall be deemed to be in transit; and
"In transit" means to transport a captive cervid through this Commonwealth by a direct route and in a continuous manner from a location out of state to another location out of state.
